    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "About Cantina:\n\nCantina Labs is a social AI company, developing a suite of advanced real-time models that push the boundaries of expression, personality, and realism. We bring characters to life, transforming how people tell stories, connect, and create. We build and power ecosystems. Cantina, our flagship social AI platform, is just the beginning.\n\nIf you're excited about the potential AI has to shape human creativity and social interactions, join us in building the future!\n\nAbout the Role:\n\nThe Head of Editorial will build and lead Cantina’s internal media organization, shaping the global conversation around Consumer AI and Social AI. This role is responsible for defining the editorial vision, producing high quality original content, and establishing Cantina Labs as a leading voice in the space. They will oversee a multidisciplinary team spanning writing, podcasting, social media, and programming, while also contributing directly as a writer and producer. The goal is to elevate the reputation of the category, spark meaningful global dialogue, and position Cantina at the center of it.\n\nWhat You’ll Do:\n\n - Define and execute a cohesive editorial strategy that drives thought leadership and shapes the public narrative around Consumer AI and Social AI\n\n - Write, edit, and produce original content across formats including long form essays, reports, newsletters, podcasts, video, and social media\n\n - Build and lead an internal media team, establishing high editorial standards, publishing cadence, and scalable workflows\n\n - Conceptualize and produce tentpole moments such as the Social AI Conference and other owned media experiences\n\n - Represent Cantina externally through speaking engagements, media appearances, and participation at major AI and technology conferences\n\nWhat You’ll Bring:\n\n - 10+ years of experience in editorial leadership, media, journalism, or content strategy, ideally within technology or emerging platforms\n\n - A strong personal writing voice and portfolio, with demonstrated ability to produce high impact, widely distributed content\n\n - Experience building and managing multidisciplinary content teams across written, audio, video, and social formats\n\n - Deep understanding of AI, consumer technology, and digital culture, with strong instincts for shaping emerging conversations\n\n - Executive presence and strategic acumen, with the ability to connect editorial efforts to brand reputation, community growth, and long term business impact\n\n - Travel up to 10% of the time\n\nCompensation:\n\nThe anticipated annual base salary range for this role is between $175,000-$230,000. When determining compensation, a number of factors will be considered, including skills, experience, job scope, location, and competitive compensation market data.\n\nBenefits:\n\n - Competitive salary and generous company equity\n\n - Medical, dental, and vision insurance – 99.99% of premiums covered by Cantina\n\n - 42 days of paid time off, including:\n   \n   - 15 PTO days\n   \n   - 10 sick days\n   \n   - 15 company holidays\n   \n   - 2 floating holidays\n\n - Generous parental leave \u0026 fertility support\n\n - 401(k) retirement savings plan\n\n - Lifestyle spending account – $500/month to use however you’d like\n\n - Complimentary lunch and snacks for in-office employees\n\n - One Medical membership, and more!",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
